Bug1.description: I don't know whyyyy she swallowed a flyyy, perhaps she'll cry from being perpetually made fun of in the form of a nursey rhyme just because she made one bad decision... er, die!

Bug2.description: Butter Fly? Get it??? Sorry... I promise I wont make this kind of joke again

Bug3.description: Honestly, I was shocked too at first when I learned that cereal in real life was harvested from Cereal Bugs. Seriously, look it up! Most cereal before 1960 were made from harvested Cereal Bug Nests!

Bug4.description: Hahaha I had my fingers crossed!

Bug5.description: I'm so tired of all these blood sucking vermin in IdleOn... and these mosquisnow bugs are annoying too!

Bug6.description: Ok these bugs are really not making any sense anymore.

Bug7.description: It's a bee and it's working. As per the Worker Bee Union Act of 35e4, I am barred from making any pun or joke about them.

Bug8.description: It glows with the joy of a being that knows it's not real, but continues to exist anyway.

Bug9.description: Amazingly, these bugs have adapted around being static images with no animation, and are able to fly without moving their wings!

Bug10.description: Wait, is this actually just a piece of dust? I mean it's classified as a bug but like, I mean... the classifiers must get it wrong sometimes right?

Critter1.description: The living embodiment of the classic cryptocurrency 'Frogecoin'. Very ribbit, much green, wow!!

Critter1A.description: Ew, it's the living embodiment of that scam alt-coin crypto ripoff, 'Frogecoin Cash'

Critter2.description: Argg, yer spendin' all me money!

Critter2A.description: Argghgg, yershpend inall memuh knee!!... Yea, mutants can't speak very well, probably on account of the radiation poisioning and all that.

Critter3.description: This cutie will stab its way into your heart if you aren't careful! No seriosuly, be careful, the bugger pricked my foot the other day and it hurt bad.

Critter3A.description: This chrome coloured scorpion came straight from the future! Fuuuutuuuuureee! FUUTUUURREE!!! SOMEONE DIRECT ME TO THE CAN OPENERRRR!!!!

Critter4.description: Adorable!!! Look how cute it's tail is, and that itty bitty nose, and the fact that it's a mouse and not a rat so I don't want to hit it with a broom!

Critter4A.description: This mole ain't got no fur! Ew, gross!! Disgusting even!!! What kind of wretched abomination has skin but no thick layer of fur??

Critter5.description: Hoot hoot! Yea thats all I got for this one.

Critter5A.description: It's a more expensive hoot, I guess. I ain't got no jokes for owls, they're too cool.

Critter6.description: It's basically just Gunter but with RTX off.

Critter6A.displayName: Eternal Lord of  The Undying Ember
Critter6A.description: Bow before the destroyer of all that lies outside his domain, the ruler of the 8th dimension and all that it's flame encompasses, the bringer of light to the blind, and darkness to those who recite his title in full. ...ah crap.

Critter7.description: It could use a carrot, the lil' guy needs some food!

Critter7A.description: The other bunny is brilliant... But I like this one more.

Critter8.description: You lean closer to the critter, and hear it say 'Dodo tshh do dodo tss dodo tss badabada dodoooo'. So no, that name isn't a typo.

Critter8A.description: Oh I guess this one is a scarab, not a beetle. You can tell because of the way it is.

Critter9A.description: One of the only beings strong enough to take on the Eternal Lord of the Undying Ember realm. Their battle would be legendary.

Critter10A.description: Yo bro I ain't touchin' that thing ain't no way!

Soul1.description: The soul moans ooOOOOooOOOoo, because it's the only key on his keyboard that works.

Soul2.description: Fat chonker this one is! It must be the moonmoon diet these ghosts have, they should start eating some of those fruits for a change!

Soul5.description: Don't judge it, you'd be mad too if someone squished YOU into that weirdo lookin' pattern!

DungeonA1.description: Yep, that leg is poisoned alright... you can tell because it's purple, and purple is gross.

DungeonA3.description: It's filled with fluid. Non potable fluid, unless you like to live danerously.

DungeonA4.description: It jiggles like it's nobody's business!

DungeonA5.description: I guess these frogs shed their tails, like how snakes shed skin, or how humans shed friendships

DungeonA6.description: The skin is so loose, you could probably strip it right off.

DungeonA7.description: So that's where his missing eyeball went...

DungeonA8.description: Huh... that vertebrae is lookin' kinda sus...

KeyFrag.description: Hold down on these to add them to your account. You'll be spending these in the next update to buy keychains at the Keychain Pile, which will be in the next update!

DungCredits1.description: Hold down to add these to your account. You can spend dungeon credits in any Dungeon Hub!

Grasslands1.description: It's often misunderstood that this is part of the spore's head. But it's actually just a stylish hat. ... well, stylish in Mushroom Culture at least.

Grasslands2.description: Imagine if humans had legs like this. Actually, it would be better if you didn't, unless you want nightmares about humans violently jumping at you from 20 feet away.

Grasslands3.description: There's something disturbing about how these beans have bones. Not as disturbing as how they also have eyeballs and walk around, but still disturbing anyway.

Grasslands4.description: It's often misunderstood that this is just the spore's stylish hat, due to the cosmetic nature of Green Spores, but this cap is actually part of this spore's head.

Jungle2.description: ''Theres a snake in me boots! Oh wait no, my boots are the snake!'' - Someone who wears snakeskin boots

Jungle3.description: Probably the only time you'll ever see a carrot cut into a cube!

Forest1.description: This item will listen to anything you have to say, it's all ears!

Forest2.description: I wonder what the Ed Boys are up to these days?

Forest3.description: Makes a loud noise when thrown at someones head, although the sound doesn't come from the horn itself...

Sewers1.description: I guess what they say about corn is true...

Sewers1b.description: Conker would have called this something else.                  NOTE: This is a very rare drop from Poops

Sewers2.description: Ew why did you pick this up?

Sewers3.description: Imagine the guy who came up with this name... ''wait, you guys HAVENT been eating this stuff?''

TreeInterior1b.description: Made of circle that's been carved into the shape of a wood.            NOTE: This is a very rare drop from Branches

TreeInterior2.description: Every time I plant one of these, someone eventually steals it and puts a fully grown tree in its place! Very annoying!

BabaYagaETC.description: Eventually you'll be able to turn these into a hatchable egg! Or maybe you already can! Or maybe you never will! Who knows what future content there may be!

DesertA1.description: This sand aint right, I tell you hwat!

DesertA1b.description: The result of letting heat and sand get it on if you know what I'm sayin.                        NOTE: This is a very rare drop from Sandy Pots

DesertA2.description: Wait a minute, this isn't a real megalodon tooth!

DesertA3.description: You could probably start a restaurant selling these! Just employ an overeager cook, give the place a cool name like The Crispy Crustacean, and you'd be set!

DesertA3b.description: Ohhhhh, that's what people mean when they say Love At First Sight!                             NOTE: This is a very rare drop from Crabcakes

DesertB1.description: How many O's are in this item's name? Yep, you're right, there's six! Good job!

DesertB2.description: It's an American Flag with red paint spilled on all the non-red bits... no wait, it's the German Flag, but they ran out of black and yellow material.

DesertB3.description: That looks sharp! Is probably what the pincermin said before you cut his arm off.

DesertC2b.description: In case you haven't noticed, these are all references to the famous early 90s videogame called Gex! This description is like a bad joke at Louis CK's house!

DesertC3.description: It's like a monocle, but not quite.

DesertC4.description: The very tippy top of the shell, with some of the underneath part attached as well.

SnowA1.description: A ball of sheep wool. Well, it used to be a ball of ice cream but then I re-drew it.

SnowA2.description: Eugh whats this WATER doing around my ice???

SnowA2a.description: Mmm yellow, my favorite flavor of snow!

SnowA3.description: Sad times I hope I remember to change this before relase.

SnowA4.description: It's got a horn stuck in it. I guess you could say this wool is kinda

SnowB2.description: No see, this is a mamOOth tusk, not a mammoth tusk, thats why you think it looks weird. Trust me, it's an incredibly drawn mamooth tusk, truly a work of art.

SnowB2a.description: The thrilling documentary that captures the first three years of Jonathan Ice's life, from birth to preschool. It also has thousands of 1 Star Ratings online claiming it's false advertising.

SnowB5.description: If you have two of these together, please be careful what other objects you put near them, I need to keep this game age appropriate!

SnowB3.description: Click the pen on, then hold it down against your desk and let go, and BAM that baby will fly you straight to the principal's office!

SnowB4.description: Ah Mr. Thermostat, not looking so hot now that I've broken you into tiny little bits... no seriously, I can't tell the temperature now that you're broken.

SnowC1.description: This vacuum operated liquid transfer system is capable of dispencing over 500 mL of dangerous dihydrogen monoxide chemical compounds from one end to the other!

SnowC2.description: Wow this is just a cheap recolouring of the normal snakeskin! I want my money back!

SnowC3.description: Uhhhh... which one which one...?? The red or the blue??? Cmon think think think.. Blue...? 'BOOOOOM'.       Wait, this is an audio cord description? Whoops, I thought this was the Bomb Defuser description!!

SnowC4.description: It's the only transparent item in IdleOn! If they weren't, they'd just be pirate eyepatches after all...

SnowC4a.description: Why yes, I have also played that game for 100s of hours since it released over 10 years ago!

SnowC5.description: Wait a minute, these are just regular bones painted red! Wait another minute, no, that's actual blood... ew.

GalaxyA1.description: According to herblore books, this purple cap is sterile. Those purple fungi that grow from the ground, however, will mutate if exposed to toxic oil radiation.

GalaxyA2.description: Oh, THATS where he put the remote, all the way out here in outer space thousands of miles from the surface! Oh that silly man!

GalaxyA2b.description: Oh, THATS why the remote wasn't working when I pushed the buttons, the batteries were all the way out here in the rare drop table!

GalaxyA3.description: WAIT NO STOP! Don't eat the rest of this donut! Think about it... if it was really worth eating, why was it left like this, all un-eaten and such? Think before you eat!

GalaxyA4.description: Rub it, maybe a genie will come out! Oh wait, you already killed the genie. Maybe try 'not murder' next time.

GalaxyB1.description: With the main prey of the Soda Can being the Soda Bottle, one can conclude that bottle caps are indigestible, and will remain untarnished after being consumed.

GalaxyB3.description: The tongue is wrapped around the bone.

GalaxyB4.description: Yo... yuhhh, yea, yea. They said I was doomed from the start, maaan ain't no wrapper made it past the worst part...

GalaxyB5.description: I wonder if this one's an undercover agent too...

GalaxyC1.description: It's a lame shell that's been desaturated due to it's unimportance.

GalaxyC1b.description: Yow wow wow! This one's got a pearl in it!!

GalaxyC2.description: It's like some sort of tentankle ball. Hang on, let me try that again. It's like some sort of tentacle ball.

GalaxyC4.description: ...37 Megawatts of electricity, if my voltmeter reading is correct!

Quest17.description: A piece of rock from the big bad wolf himself. Careful, it's overflowing with green plasma energy! No wait, that's just some moss.

Quest29.description: A piece of rock from the bigger badder wolf himself. Careful, it's overflowing with poisonous ooze! No wait, that's just plasma energy...

EfauntDrop1.description: A piece of Efaunt's tunic. I guess it must have gotten torn off while you were absolutely obliterating them with big time Damage.

EfauntDrop2.description: Chaotic Efaunt is probably glad you removed a few of his ribs, for uhh... various reasons.

Chiz0.description: A spike from Chizoar's neck. It's ice cold, and sharp as a tack.

Chiz1.description: A spike from Chaotic Chizoar's neck. Despite it being made of ice, it burns at the touch due to its acidity.

TrollPart.description: Even the scales look like they have a wry smile, almost as if it remembers the part it played in that infamous tutorial prank you were unfortunately involved in

LavaA1.description: Poor suggma slug, couldn't even handle a little bit of water eh?

LavaA1b.description: Huh... was uh... was that one some sort of king or something? This species really needs to sort out its heirarchy, it didn't look any different from the others!

LavaA2.description: Look if you're gonna kill the poor thing, you may as well have the decency of finishing the whole thing!

LavaA3.description: Reduced to mere glass fragments... I guess thats just the price he pays for being a monster, his destiny was calling.

LavaA4.description: Thats not your cheese! Err, thats nacho cheese! Ok wow that really doesn't work typed out like that...

LavaA5.description: It's got a built in gyroscope to help with balance. Unfortunately, it isn't turned on.
